                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.918/24.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-09T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 9, 1912—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s March 29, 7 p.m. Inquire whether any relief can be expected as to
                    censorship of very conservative Associated Press service. What answer has
                    Mexican Government made as to its general policy in the matter?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
